message.content:
Below is one way to “read off” the finished model from the two images and then match it to the block dictionary.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
•  Block Count and Layers
   – There are 9 total blocks in a single layer.  
   – At the very center is 1 green block (the small green square you see on top).  
   – Surrounding it in a “plus‑sign” arrangement are 4 blue blocks.  
   – Outside each blue block (again in a crosslike layout) are 4 orange wedges.  

•  Spatial Relationships
   – Center: The green block sits alone in the middle.  
   – Blue Ring: Each of the four sides of the green cube touches one blue cube, forming a plus sign around the center.  
   – Orange Outer Ring: Each orange piece is aligned radially outward from the blue “arms,” giving the structure its four orange “wings.”  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING THE BLOCKS (BY INDEX FROM THE DICTIONARY)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below are the exact blocks (with color and orientation) needed.  We cannot rotate any of them ourselves, so each piece must be used exactly as‐pictured:

•  Green Center  
   – Use block #2 (the green cube) for the middle.  

•  Four Blue Arms  
   – Use block #7 for each of the four blue arms.  
     (All are the same blue cube in the same orientation as depicted in index #7.)  

•  Four Orange Wedges  
   – Use blocks #13, #14, #15, and #16 (the four orange wedges, each in its own orientation).  
     These four together yield the “four‐way” wedge arrangement seen in the target.  

Hence your final block list and their dictionary indices:
   { 2, 7, 7, 7, 7, 13, 14, 15, 16 }

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‑BY‑STEP ASSEMBLY INSTRUCTIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Use the following sequence (one possible order) to build the structure from the ground up:

{
   Step1: Move block with index 2   // Place the green cube at center
   Step2: Move block with index 7   // First blue arm
   Step3: Move block with index 7   // Second blue arm
   Step4: Move block with index 7   // Third blue arm
   Step5: Move block with index 7   // Fourth blue arm
   Step6: Move block with index 13  // First orange wedge
   Step7: Move block with index 14  // Second orange wedge
   Step8: Move block with index 15  // Third orange wedge
   Step9: Move block with index 16  // Fourth orange wedge
}

Following these steps (and using **each block exactly as pictured** in the dictionary) reproduces the target arrangement shown in the first image.
